title: Women's Racing Clinic presented by CRCA
description:
Each year as part of CRCA’s coaching and development program the club hosts a Women’s Clinic designed to introduce women to the club and bicycle racing.  Many of the City’s elite racers have been introduced to the sport via the Women’s clinic, including current pro cyclist and national time trial champion Evelyn Stevens.  For more on Evelyn’s story see this Bicycling article.

Participants in the Women’s Clinic are encouraged to explore the club’s various other women’s racing activities, which include the new Women’s Cat 3/4 series, the new Women’s Cat 4 series and an expanded Coaching program, including women-only sessions.
course: Central Park
registration: All registration via Bikereg. No day of registration.

GVCC Wednesday Cross Training Series
description: Wednesday Night Cyclocross training series
course: Learn to negotiate barriers (mount/dismount efficiently) and become comfortable with varied terrain on rolling wooded and open single track at the YMCA\'s Camp Arrowhead.  This is a non-competitive event.  No results,   Just learning.
registration: Show up on the day of the event.  Donate $25 to the YMCA for 1 or all training events.  Sign a release form every time you train with the group.  Must be a member of GVCC and hold a USAC license in good standing.
notes: Non Competitive.  No separation by gender or ability.  Guidance provided by experienced GVCC members and members can then practice on their own.
